### Description

Angular 21 with Vtest does not collect code coverage.

----

### Repro steps

Run the following commands:

1. `ng new "test-app-vitest" --package-manager "npm" --skip-git --style "scss" --no-ssr --ai-config "none" --test-runner "vitest"`
2. `cd test-app-vitest`
3. `npm install --save-dev @vitest/coverage-v8`
4. `npm run test -- --no-watch --coverage`

Check code coverage report (command output) - 0%.

#### Remarks

1. It is possible to add the entire code base to code coverage report by updating `angular.json`:

``` json
{
  "projects": {
    "test-app-vitest": {
      "architect": {
        "test": {
          "builder": "@angular/build:unit-test",
          "options": {
            "coverageInclude": [
              "src/**/*.ts"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

but code coverage is always 0%

2. Other reporters produce the same output (0% coverage). Tried with `cobertura` and `lcov` - `angular.json`:

``` json
{
  "projects": {
    "test-app-vitest": {
      "architect": {
        "test": {
          "builder": "@angular/build:unit-test",
          "options": {
            "coverageInclude": [
              "src/**/*.ts"
            ],
            "coverageReporters": [
              "cobertura",
              "lcov"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

3. There is no difference when configuring code coverage in `vitest-base.config.ts` comparing to `angular.json`

``` json
// angulat.json

{
  "projects": {
    "test-app-vitest": {
      "architect": {
        "test": {
          "builder": "@angular/build:unit-test",
          "options": {
            "runnerConfig": "vitest-base.config.ts"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

``` ts
// vitest-base.config.ts

import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    passWithNoTests: true,
    coverage: {
      include: [
        'src/**/*.ts'
      ],
      reporter: [
        'cobertura',
        'lcov'
      ]
    }
  }
});
```

